          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for recitation and contemplation and is a poetic exploration of the amorous relationship between the Hindu deities Kṛṣṇa and Rādhā. Kṛṣṇa is presented not as an avatar of Viṣṇu, but as the essence of the universe itself. First literary work to develop fully the figure of Rādhā, the cow herdess, and her relationship with Kṛṣṇa. Poem is often approached as a devotional text by modern Vaiṣṇavas.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Gītagovinda</title>
              <author>Jayadeva, active 12th century</author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīgītagoviṃde jayadevaviracite māhākāvyekhādhīnabhartṛkāvarṇane sraprītāṃ varonāmadvādaśaḥ sargaḥ // 12 // 1919 (f. 19r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
